The consensus recommendation, according to Zacks Investment research, is 2.3. Chicago Bridge & Iron Company N.V. (NYSE:CBI) has trailing twelve month Return on Assets of -4.6%, which is key indicator of how profitable a company is relative to its total assets. (NYSE:CBI) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Monday, May 8th. Insiders have sold 53,857 shares of company stock worth $1,671,028 in the last quarter. "(CAT), Chicago Bridge & Iron Company NV (CBI) and Apache ..." on June 21, 2017. The business's revenue for the quarter was down 11.4% on a year-over-year basis.A number of other research analysts have also issued reports on CBI.

